    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your<strong> cucumber</strong> lengthways finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> and <strong>chopped dill</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span>[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up, then set aside to pickle – this is your<strong> quick-pickled dill cucumber</strong></p>",
